[The take away messages from this week's polio statistics again is good news and not so good news.

The good news includes:
- No additional cases of cVDPV identified in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.
- No new WPV1 cases reported from Pakistan or Nigeria (2 of the 3 remaining polio endemic countries).
- Total count of WPV1 cases reported to date in 2017 is 12 compared with 37 cases reported in all of 2016.

The not so good news includes:
- 1 newly confirmed case of WPV1 associated paralytic polio in Afghanistan.
- 2 positive environmental samples for WPV1 in Afghanistan in provinces with no recent WPV1 cases in either province.
- 3 positive environmental samples for WPV1 in Pakistan involving 2 provinces.
- 4 newly confirmed cVDPV2 cases in Deir Ez-Zor governorate, bringing the total number of cVDPV cases reported by Syria to 52. Dates of onset of disease were in late August 2017, so results from AFP (acute flaccid paralysis) surveillance in September 2017 are still pending. An additional isolate from a healthy child was also positive for WPV1.

A map showing the global distribution of all WPV1 associated cases and cVDPV associated cases can be found at http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

HealthMap/ProMED maps can be found at:
Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5391927,140
Afghanistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5391927,137
Syria: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5391927,86

In addition to the weekly report of the Global Polio Eradication Initiative, there are 2 interesting media reports. In one report, "Amid Fear and Guns, Polio Finds a Refuge" is an excellent overview of the current challenges facing eradication of polio globally with a focus on the challenges of the civil unrest in the 3 remaining polio endemic countries, using primarily Nigeria as the case study location. A lengthy but well thought out article available at: https://undark.org/article/polio-nigeria-boko-haram/. The second article has a focus on Pakistan and the challenges facing vaccination activities there http://www.arabnews.com/node/1180356/world. - Mod.MPP]
